        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>directly struck idiophones [300041659], struck idiophones [300041657], idiophones [300041646], sound devices by acoustical characteristics [300041621], sound devices (equipment) [300387677], Sound Devices (hierarchy name) [300041619], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Instruments sounded by being struck either with a nonsonorous body, such as a stick or hand, or against a nonsonorous object, such as the human body or the ground.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000026541/Marcuse, Musical Instruments Dictionary (1975)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Slaginstrumenten; bespeeld door ze aan te slaan met een niet-klinkend voorwerp, zoals een stok of een hand, ook door ze te slaan tegen een niet-klinkend voorwerp, zoals het menselijk lichaam of de grond.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052453/Algemene muziekencyclopedie (1961)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052452/Encyclopedie van muziekinstrumenten (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>亦或以棍棒或手這類不會發聲的物體敲打，亦或敲擊人體或地面等不發聲物體發聲的樂器。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tonerzeugendes Instrument, das entweder durch Anschlagen mit einem nichtklingenden Körper, wie ein Stock oder eine Hand, oder durch Schlagen gegen ein nichtklingendes Objekt, wie der menschliche Körper oder der Boden, zum Klingen gebracht wird.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
